                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.7962/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-24T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 24, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1308. Department’s 761, July 18, 7 p.m. In view of the special position of the
                    British in Saudi Arabia, the personal prestige of the British Minister and the
                    fact that he has in the past discussed with Saudi Arabian officials the matter
                    of air routes and fields in the country, I have recommended to Moose that he
                    cooperate closely with Bird in the pending negotiations on this matter. Any
                    other course would result in confusion and delay.</p>
                <p>Minister of State Casey is sending appropriate instructions in the premises to
                    the British Minister at Jidda.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Jidda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
